President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate John Nalbandian as a member of the Board of Directors of the State Justice Institute. Nalbandian is currently a partner in the Litigation Department of Taft Stettinius & Hollister LLP, specializing in appellate and general litigation in state and federal courts. He has experience in various legal areas, including antitrust, products liability, intellectual property, employment, white collar crime, and class actions. Nalbandian is a member of several state and district bars and has been recognized by Cincinnati Magazine as a Super Lawyers Rising Star. He is also listed in The Best Lawyers in America in Appellate Law and has been certified by the Ohio State Bar Association as a specialist in Appellate Law. Nalbandian graduated from the University of Virginia School of Law and earned his undergraduate degree from the University of Pennsylvania, Wharton School.